            <section class="section point wrapper" id="point-1">
                <div class="grid item">
                    <h4 class="grid__1-4">I'm Frank Hulley-Jones</h4>
                    <p class="grid__2-3">
                        I'm the design lead of The Guardian Visuals team. I
                        currently spend my time creating visual interactives and
                        features, splitting my time 50/50 between design and
                        development. Here's 3 ways I can help the Google Design
                        team.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <a href="#point-2" class="js-scroll scroll-to"></a>
            </section>
            <section class="section point wrapper" id="point-2">
                <div class="grid item">
                    <h4 class="grid__1-4">I strive for design consistency</h4>
                    <p class="grid__2-3">
                        One of the main contributions I’ve brought to the
                        Visuals team is introducing a design system that not
                        only improves the user experience of articles but the
                        designer and developer experience too. It sounds simple,
                        but a reduced colour palette, a limited number of
                        typographic styles and a design template meant each time
                        our team produced an interactive we weren’t reinventing
                        the wheel.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <a href="#point-3" class="js-scroll scroll-to"></a>
            </section>

            <section class="section point wrapper" id="point-3">
                <div class="grid item">
                    <h4 class="grid__1-4">Collaboration is key</h4>
                    <p class="grid__2-3">
                        I believe the best design is all about good storytelling
                        and the best way to tell a good story is through
                        collaboration — whether it is working alongside
                        photographers, animators, journalists and fellow coders
                        to make the most out of their expertise, or mentoring
                        designers and engineers to help them reach their
                        potential. I relish the opportunity to produce
                        innovative interactive experiences that excite and
                        challenge audiences (and sometimes even
                        <a
                            href="https://www.dandad.org/awards/professional/2019/graphic-design/231385/the-guardian-the-internet-but-not-as-we-know-it/"
                            >win awards</a
                        >).
                    </p>
                </div>
                <a href="#point-4" class="js-scroll scroll-to"></a>
            </section>

            <section class="section point wrapper" id="point-4">
                <div class="grid item">
                    <h4 class="grid__1-4">I have a distinctive voice</h4>
                    <p class="grid__2-3">
                        When approaching a project, I try to bring elements of
                        playfulness into my work. Whether that’s through a
                        <a
                            href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/ng-interactive/2020/may/20/relax-to-the-sounds-of-british-wildlife"
                            >charming illustration</a
                        >,
                        <a
                            href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/ng-interactive/2019/may/17/air-pollution-may-be-damaging-every-organ-and-cell-in-the-body-finds-global-review"
                            >clever animation</a
                        >
                        or
                        <a
                            href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/ng-interactive/2019/jan/11/the-internet-but-not-as-we-know-it-life-online-in-china-russia-cuba-and-india"
                            >hidden idea</a
                        >. People have such little time and such short attention
                        spans, so if you can create something that rewards them
                        for pausing and exploring, I believe they become more
                        engaged, intrigued and more willing to dedicate the
                        little time they have.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <a href="#g-header" class="js-scroll scroll-to"></a>
            </section>
